@startuml
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam BoxPadding 12
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam SequenceGroupBodyBackgroundColor #F5F5F5

title D4 - Energy Analytics\nentity owner: EnergyAnalytics

participant "Camunda\n(Sprint 2)" as CAM
participant "Telemetry MS\nentity: TelemetryEvent" as TMS
participant "Prosumer MS\nentity: Prosumer" as PMS
participant "UtilityOperator MS\nentity: UtilityOperator" as UMS
participant "Energy\nAnalytics MS\nentity: EnergyAnalytics" as EAM
participant "Kafka 4.1.1" as K
database "AWS RDS" as DB

note over CAM,EAM : Sprint 1: REST call direct to Energy Analytics MS\nSprint 2: Camunda process EnergyAnalytics\norchestrates calls via Kong REST Connector

== Business process: cross-entity logic (Camunda responsibility) ==
CAM -> TMS : GET /telemetry/history?period=X
TMS --> CAM : [telemetry records]

CAM -> PMS : GET /prosumers?gridCellId=X
PMS --> CAM : [{prosumerId, assetId}]

CAM -> UMS : GET /gridcells
UMS --> CAM : [{gridCellId, maxCapacityKw}]

CAM -> EAM : POST /energy-analytics\n{period, telemetryData,\nprosumersData, gridCellsData}

== Energy Analytics MS: internal logic on EnergyAnalytics entity ==
EAM -> EAM : Compute (own entity rules):\n- Energy Discharged by Zone\n- Generated Energy by Prosumer\n- Consumed Energy by Prosumer\n- Average SoC

EAM -> DB : UPSERT energy_analytics\n{period, gridCellId, prosumerId, metrics}

EAM -> K : produce to EnergyDischargedByZone\n{gridCellId, energyKwh, period}
EAM -> K : produce to GeneratedEnergyByProsumer\n{prosumerId, energyKwh, period}
EAM -> K : produce to ConsumedEnergyByProsumer\n{prosumerId, energyKwh, period}
EAM -> K : produce to AverageSoC\n{gridCellId, avgSocPercent, period}

EAM --> CAM : 201 {analyticsId}

== Internal endpoints on EnergyAnalytics entity ==
note over EAM : GET /energy-analytics?gridCellId=X&period=Y\nGET /energy-analytics/stats\n(min/max/avg per zone and prosumer)\nGET /energy-analytics/trends?prosumerId=X

@enduml
